properties.documentation: \brief Abstract base class for AutoModeController and ManualModeController
Helper class to track and draw bounding boxes on screen.
\brief This struct is used during communication between DriveCommandPublishers and DriveCommandSubscribers

documentation.value: the DriveCommandSubscriber can use this to assign priorities to the modules

properties.documentation: \brief This class can receive DriveCommand structs, prioritizes them by their source and forwards the values to the DriveController once updateMotor() gets called.
\brief Base class for all classes that are able to publish DriveCommands to a DriveCommandSubscriber

documentation.value: used for the source field in DriveCommand messages.

properties.documentation: \brief DriveCommandSubscribers can receive DriveCommand structs from objects that are derived from DriveCommandPublisher
\brief This module can be active in manual and in auto mode. It rotates the TivSeg until it detects at least one marker.

documentation.value: maximum time this module can work in blocking mode until it aborts
used in blocking mode to abort operation

properties.documentation: \brief Only used in Automode. This module retrieves the markerList from the SensorManager, checks for markers and tries to follow the one with the best confidence until it loses track of it. After that, it uses the next marker that has the highest confidence.
\brief This module is used for blocking drive operations via terminal command or script and can only be invoked via terminal.

documentation.value: Detection confidence. Range is 0 to 100; 0 is worst, 100 is best.
